Description:
    Generates a complete in-app notification system using the Noticed gem.
    Supports both user-scoped and account-scoped notifications.

Features:
    - In-app notification bell with unread count
    - Notification list view with mark read functionality
    - Example notifier classes (WelcomeNotifier)
    - Notification preferences settings page
    - Database-backed notifications via Noticed gem

Example:
    bin/rails generate boilermaker:notifications

    You will be prompted to choose a scope:
      [1] Account - Notifications scoped to teams/organizations
      [2] User    - Notifications scoped to individual users

    This will create:
        app/models/concerns/notifiable.rb
        app/controllers/notifications_controller.rb
        app/views/notifications/index.rb
        app/views/settings/notifications.rb
        app/components/notification_bell.rb
        app/components/notification_item.rb
        app/notifiers/application_notifier.rb
        app/notifiers/welcome_notifier.rb
        app/controllers/concerns/notifications_feature.rb
        config/routes/notifications.rb
        test/controllers/notifications_controller_test.rb

Options:
    --skip-routes   Skip generating route file
    --skip-tests    Skip generating test files
    --skip-config   Skip updating boilermaker.yml
    --skip-seeds    Skip adding seed data

Creating Custom Notifications:
    1. Create a new notifier in app/notifiers/:

       class CommentNotifier < ApplicationNotifier
         deliver_by :database
         deliver_by :email, mailer: "NotificationMailer"

         notification_methods do
           def message
             "#{params[:commenter].name} commented on your post"
           end
         end
       end

    2. Send the notification:
       CommentNotifier.with(commenter: user, post: post).deliver(post.author)

Integration:
    Add the notification bell to your navigation:
    render Components::NotificationBell.new(recipient: Current.user)
